While I like this app for its ability to easily print out, say, an email, word doc, or pdf right from my phone (it IS SUPER reliable for documents and pdfs!); it is SERIOUSLY lacking in the photo printout department. This app offers a "document" or a "photo" option. The "document" option I really have no complaints for: you can choose from within the app the color, quality, quantity, and size of the page you want to print. You can also elect double-sided printing. Under the "photo" option, though, you can't do much. Options are pretty much limited to quality, quantity, "borderless print," and "fit to page"/"shrink to fit." There is no option in the app to print multiple copies/pages per sheet of paper. Nor can you dictate the actual dimensions of the image you wish to print. You will get a letter-sized image. Or several. Period. Those are all of your choices. I'd really like to see them add options for dimensions of photos, as my HP printer does an excellent job of printing photos (with the assistance of another app like Picasa [outdated, I know] that dictates photo print-size and copies per sheet thereof). However, without an extraneous app exporting ready-made, multiple per-sheet photos, you will not be able to execute that from within this mobile app.
